import{_ as e,o as t,c as o,N as a}from"./chunks/framework.cd9250a1.js";const c=JSON.parse('{"title":"Speak English With Tiffani","description":"","frontmatter":{},"headers":[],"relativePath":"english/youtube/Tiffani.md"}'),i={name:"english/youtube/Tiffani.md"},n=a('<h1 id="speak-english-with-tiffani" tabindex="-1">Speak English With Tiffani <a class="header-anchor" href="#speak-english-with-tiffani" aria-label="Permalink to &quot;Speak English With Tiffani&quot;">‚Äã</a></h1><p><a href="https://www.youtube.com/@SpeakEnglishWithTiffani" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer">Let&#39;s go to Tiffani&#39;s channel ~ üò∏</a></p><p>Tiffani has a great passion for teaching English. I truly admire her enthusiastic spirit, and it deeply touches my heart. I enjoy her story time immensely as it often brings back memories of my childhood and past experiences. If you&#39;re learning English, I highly recommend Tiffani&#39;s lessons. It is both enjoyable and educational. Give it a try!</p><h3 id="ü§çsmall-talk-and-deeper-conversations" tabindex="-1">ü§çsmall talk and deeper conversations <a class="header-anchor" href="#ü§çsmall-talk-and-deeper-conversations" aria-label="Permalink to &quot;ü§çsmall talk and deeper conversations&quot;">‚Äã</a></h3><p><a href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=dfjImIm2iPU&amp;t=1639s" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer">Here is the link to this course.üòº</a></p><h4 id="small-talk" tabindex="-1">SMALL TALK <a class="header-anchor" href="#small-talk" aria-label="Permalink to &quot;SMALL TALK&quot;">‚Äã</a></h4><ul><li><p>Small talk is basically meant to be light and fun.</p><p>It is a way for 2 (or more)people to talk to each other,without really getting to know the other.</p></li><li><p>In this type of conversation,no personal questions are usually asked. Usually the only emotions involved are happy or neutral. Does not lead to the individuals truly getting to know each other.</p></li></ul><h4 id="deep-conversation" tabindex="-1">DEEP CONVERSATION <a class="header-anchor" href="#deep-conversation" aria-label="Permalink to &quot;DEEP CONVERSATION&quot;">‚Äã</a></h4><ul><li><p>Deep conversation is meant to be deep and thought provoking.</p><p>It is a way for 2(or more) people to talk to each other and truly understand how the other thinks</p></li><li><p>Enables the individuals to truly get to know each other on a deeper level. It usually requires deep thought and a certain opinion to be expressed. Allows a person to express their true feelings about a certain topic.</p></li></ul><div class="tip custom-block"><p class="custom-block-title">TIP</p><p>üòÄ Conversation is back and forth.</p></div><p>Here are three things you should remember :</p><h5 id="don-t-dominate" tabindex="-1">DON&#39;T DOMINATE <a class="header-anchor" href="#don-t-dominate" aria-label="Permalink to &quot;DON&#39;T DOMINATE&quot;">‚Äã</a></h5><p>The first thing to remember is to never dominate the conversation. It is important to make sure there is a balance between you and the person you are speaking to.</p><ol><li>Dominating shows that you don&#39;t care about the other person&#39;s opinion.</li><li>People don&#39;t want to have conversations with people who dominate the conversation.</li><li>It also shows that your listening skills are not good</li></ol><h5 id="listen-attentively" tabindex="-1">LISTEN ATTENTIVELY <a class="header-anchor" href="#listen-attentively" aria-label="Permalink to &quot;LISTEN ATTENTIVELY&quot;">‚Äã</a></h5><p>The second thing to remember is that listening skills are an important part of effective communication. In other words, listening attentively will actually help you to master English conversation.</p><ol><li>Listening attentively will help you to understand people better.</li><li>As you listen,you actually improve your English ability, because you are taking in new information</li><li>If you listen well, the other person will also want to listen to you.</li></ol><h5 id="don-t-interrupt" tabindex="-1">DON&#39;T INTERRUPT <a class="header-anchor" href="#don-t-interrupt" aria-label="Permalink to &quot;DON&#39;T INTERRUPT&quot;">‚Äã</a></h5><p>The third thing to remember is to never interrupt(ÊâìÊñ≠). This is because interrupting someone,or suddenly stopping them,is rude and can stop a conversation.</p><ol><li>People don&#39;t want to talk to someone who constantly interrupts them.</li><li>Interrupting someone shows that you are not listening to them.</li><li>It also hinders the flow of conversation, because it shows that you think your words are more important.</li></ol><h5 id="type-experience" tabindex="-1">TYPE EXPERIENCE <a class="header-anchor" href="#type-experience" aria-label="Permalink to &quot;TYPE EXPERIENCE&quot;">‚Äã</a></h5><ol><li>Say the name of the person you are speaking with. Example &quot;<strong>Well Brian,it was so great speaking with you..</strong>.&quot;</li><li>Briefly mention the experience they told you about again. Example &quot;<strong>I really enjoyed hearing about your trip to Paris...</strong>&quot;</li><li>Relate it to yourself and something about the future very quickly. Example&quot;<strong>Hopefully I will be able to visit there in the future as well...</strong>&quot;</li></ol><h5 id="example" tabindex="-1"><strong>example</strong> <a class="header-anchor" href="#example" aria-label="Permalink to &quot;**example**&quot;">‚Äã</a></h5><ul><li>Well Tiff,it has been amazing speaking with you. I can imagine how much fun you got with your sister. may be when my sister come back we will try rapping together.</li><li>Well Alex,it was so great speaking with you. I really enjoyed hearing about your games. Hopefully I will be able to play some funny video games with you.</li></ul><h5 id="type-feelings" tabindex="-1">TYPE FEELINGS <a class="header-anchor" href="#type-feelings" aria-label="Permalink to &quot;TYPE FEELINGS&quot;">‚Äã</a></h5><ol><li>Say the name of the person you are speaking with. Example &quot;<strong>Wow Mary,I truly enjoyed speaking with you...</strong>&quot;</li><li>Briefly mention the feelings they told you about again. Example&quot;<strong>It was very interesting listening to how you felt about...</strong>&quot;</li><li>Mention the importance of that feeling and lead into another future conversation. Example&quot;<strong>I also believe it is very important. Hopefully we can talk more about it soon...</strong>&quot;</li></ol><h5 id="example-1" tabindex="-1"><strong>example</strong> <a class="header-anchor" href="#example-1" aria-label="Permalink to &quot;**example**&quot;">‚Äã</a></h5><ul><li>Wow Tiffany,I really loved to talk with you,it was very interesting listening to how you felt about your amazing marriage. I also believe it is very important to create a great relationship with love,respect and communication. Hopefully we can talk more in the future</li><li>Well Tiff I really enjoy to speak with you about your marriage, It seems like you both love each other,I believe love is important too. Hopefully we can talk more about love in the future.</li><li>Wow Alex, I truly enjoyed speaking with you. It was very interesting listening to how you felt about your favorite game. It is really funny and impressive. I also believe it is very important. Hopefully we can talk more about it soon.</li></ul><h3 id="ü§ç10-real-english-sentences-to-use-every-day" tabindex="-1">ü§ç10 REAL ENGLISH SENTENCES TO USE EVERY DAY <a class="header-anchor" href="#ü§ç10-real-english-sentences-to-use-every-day" aria-label="Permalink to &quot;ü§ç10 REAL ENGLISH SENTENCES TO USE EVERY DAY&quot;">‚Äã</a></h3><p><a href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=NOdIdz1Sugw" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer">Here is the link to this course.üòº</a></p><ol><li>Would you mind if I called you back in a few minutes (an hour) ?</li><li>I&#39;m not quite sure I caught what you said. Would you mind repeating it one more time?</li><li>Thank you for asking. But I am going to have to pass at this time.</li><li>Can I help you with anything in particular?</li><li>Hey. How did things go with..? <em>- Hey, how did things go with your job interview yesterday?</em></li><li>Do you happen to know how to ...? <em>- Do you happen to know how to troubleshoot(‰øÆÁêÜ) a computer network issue?</em></li><li>It was a pleasure meeting you. I look forward to speaking with you again in the future</li><li>I&#39;m a little swamped at work.</li><li>Would you mind lending/giving me a hand with...? <em>- Would you mind giving me a hand with moving the furniture to the new apartment?</em></li><li>Is there anything in particular that you would like to..? <em>- Is there anything in particular that you would like to learn during this training program?</em></li></ol>',31),l=[n];function r(s,h,u,p,d,m){return t(),o("div",null,l)}const g=e(i,[["render",r]]);export{c as __pageData,g as default};
